reviews.text: The scenery was beautiful and our waiter was friendly, but the food was very disappointing. I ordered the fish tacos and they came with a tiny 50 cent piece sized fish. They menu said they had cilantro lime dressing, but there was only plain cream and some brown guacamole-like substance. It was all so sadly bland.  The tortillas were cold from a package, not even warmed on the grill! The bulk of it was coleslaw. $15 for packaged coleslaw in a cold tortilla.  The kids‚Äô burgers were big, but again we had to ask for things like lettuce, tomatoes, onions, mustard, ketchup‚Ä¶ standard burger stuff you would think would be included.  Nothing felt like a whole meal. Be prepared for JUST Mac and cheese, no sides or flourishes. JUST a burger patty between a bun. We ate at many other much better places in the area.

First before I talk about how bad our steak was I‚Äôll say the server was fantastic very attentive and professional this establishment should be happy to have her. On to the bad my Boyfriend and I both ordered the sirloin med rare and same sides, our steaks first came med well and well done. ( we also didn‚Äôt eat more then one bite before we asked to have it done the way we ordered. The steaks they sent out to replace were just unfortunately full of tendons and one was grey. We got to go boxes paid the full bill plus just shy of twenty percent tip because again the service was great, I can‚Äôt say I‚Äôll ever come again because it just was not worth 28 dollars a steak.
The food was exceptional. My fiance raved about the pulled pork nachos while I had  the walleye. All staff was friendly and welcoming. Our server was great, prompt and helpful.

Great location on the golf course, with indoor and outdoor seating. The restaurant is clean and has a nice atmosphere. Staff are helpful and provided us excellent service. The Local has the best appetizers in town and a creative menu that offers something for everyone. They offer weekly trivia, specials, events and fun activities. Good restaurant for couples, families, and groups.

Being a tourist to Ashland, WI and counting this as one of my favorite cities to vacation, I can say there are much better places to eat in the area.  This is just okay.  Nothing to write home or even post about to be honest.  It is a golf course bar in a small blue collar town that serves food.  The food here is too much of a promise for the grill and not enough on follow-through.  Save your money and eat elsewhere.  This is a better place if you golf and just drink.

detailedReviews.text: My salmon was pretty good.  The salad bar had a large variety of toppings.  The potato rings were amazing.  My husband had steak and it was slightly overcooked and FYI, they don't have steak sauce.  The view was nice with the water.  Reasonably priced and my husband and I both enjoyed our meals and will be back.

detailedReviews.text: Very enjoyable dinner. Great service! NY strip was delicious and tender. The cannoli's were amazing! Mashed potatoes were different, not the usual kind made with milk and kind of dry, but my husband LOVED the potato rings! Highly recommend

detailedReviews.text: Favorite restaurant in Ashland sometimes can be a little slow but best cheese curds you will find

detailedReviews.author: Kira Castle
detailedReviews.text:
Great all you can eat buffet for Easter...$30. Nice desserts & salad bar.
Included prime rib & crab legs! Located at the golf club.

detailedReviews.author: Sara Mark
detailedReviews.text:
**Edit** They added a vegan burger! It comes automatically vegan (no cheese or mayo), which is great. We even inquired about the gluten free bun and they were so happy to help. The salad bar is fantastic and such a great price. I also heard they are working on their NA drink options! They changed this place so much and their hardwork has paid off. It's so cool.

This place is so nice in the summer! The patio is great and the service is fabulous. I wish they had some vegan options though! I would come all the time if I could eat something other than fries and salad!

detailedReviews.author: Randy Raprager
detailedReviews.text: The atmosphere leaves a little to be desired. The restroom needs to be cleaned. The food was good and the prices were very reasonable.

detailedReviews.author: Stephanie S
detailedReviews.text:
Moral of the review: highly recommend!

What we had: the prime rib sandwich and the Alfredo with salmon added, and two brandy old fashioneds.

The service was very fast and very friendly. Had good conversations with the bar tender and the waitress.

The drinks: some of the best brandy old fashioneds we've had! (and it's our go to everywhere)

The food: the food was excellent! The salmon Alfredo rivaled a dish i had in France. The prime rib sandwich was excellent, too! Highly recommend both options. We were both very happy with our choices and will order both again next time we come in.

The atmosphere: it was a quiet evening, an hour or so prior to closing. It was quiet and friendly. I'm sure with or without the house being packed, we would have the same wonderful fast service! The bartender (with great hair) and the waitress (with the wonderful smile) were fantastic and made the night a great experience!

(only addition i would recommend to the establishment is adding a new special - could be once a month - with two salmon types on the same alfredo plate - the current salmon plus some smoked salmon and a little extra parm - then you'll beat the dish I had in France!)

detailedReviews.author: leanne wilson

detailedReviews.text: Basic Friday deep fried fish dinner.

detailedReviews.author: Aaron Colborn
detailedReviews.text: We stopped in to have lunch on our way to Hurley, and we had never been to the local before. When we drove up, we found that it was on a golf course. We walked in, and there was no hostess, but the girl behind the bar told us to sit anywhere. There was a wait before we were able to order and we found out that the bartender was having to cover both, but we each ordered a bloody mary, and I had the Philly sandwich and onion rings my wife had the alfredo. The drinks came, and I have to say that it was in the top 3 worst Bloody Mary's I have ever had. Just plain tomato juice and vodka. Needless to say, we didn't have high expectations for the food. Our order came out, and I was pleasantly surprised. My sandwich was huge, and the onion rings were really good. My wife raved about the alfredo sauce and still says that it was the best she has tasted. The atmosphere was kind of lacking. It had that we just opened kind of feel like they tossed some booths against the wall and set up some tables.

detailedReviews.author: Elizabeth Macky
detailedReviews.text: Grateful to have a real life Cheers! üçª

detailedReviews.author: John Stahre
detailedReviews.text: Ceasarsallad was good. Vine was good.  View is great and the company was awesome. We came as a big dropin company (8 people) and it was ok. Weather was beatiful and there was empty seats outside with a great view. We asked for a table outside, and we got a table inside, at least I could see my friends. I felt like they wanted to get rid of us fast. I got a fastfood feeling. The bill came before we finished our food, and when we finished our food and left there still was empty outside.

detailedReviews.author: Thomas Keeley
detailedReviews.text:
The place was mostly empty and we had to wait 40 min for it drinks.  When we asked if someone could help us we were told, "I don't know who is supposed to have that section, but it isn't me.". Usually this is a good place to go, but this time was very very disappointing

Update:  so we have come back s few times since the original post.  Mostly, experiences have been good.  But tonight, we hit a new low sadly.

Ordered the 10 oz sirloin, asked for it to be rare.  I'm attaching a pic of it, but at best, this is medium well.  And, this was their second attempt and the manager said "we are not doing it again because we don't know how to cook it that way.". Really?!

If you go here, order the cheese curds, the swedish meatballs, or wait for the prime rib special.  Don't get the steak unless you like hockey puck cooking.

detailedReviews.author: John Bainbridge
detailedReviews.text: Great selection and delicious food!

detailedReviews.author: Michelle Davidson
detailedReviews.text: The Mother's Day delivery was OUTSTANDING! The fact that all four local businesses joined together and provided some amazing gifts was much appreciated. I can't say enough about how wonderful this was!! Thanks again!!

detailedReviews.author: Jason S
detailedReviews.text: Great food, excellent salad bar.  Soup was unbelievably good.

detailedReviews.author: Emily Matchey
detailedReviews.text: Stopped for an early dinner here and we had exceptional service and amazing food. Super clean and nice place with really reasonable prices for what you get. Great salad bar and soups, wonderful sandwiches, and the prime rib was outstanding. Loved it! Oh and the cheese curds were phenomonal!

detailedReviews.text: We had a group of approximately 20 in Ashland for hockey college game. The staff was welcoming and super friendly! Wish I would‚Äôve caught their names but they were amazing. Food and drinks were good. Beautiful ambiance with the bar overlooking golf course. Outstanding service! Great Bloody Mary!

detailedReviews.author: Joshua K

detailedReviews.text: If I could give 0 stars I would. Racist and disgusting. Being asked if ‚Äúwatermelon and fried chicken‚Äù was a preferred meal as the only black person at the table while the rest of the table ordered from the menu was dehumanizing. Will never eat here again and will warn others so they don‚Äôt pay to deal with the same harassment.

detailedReviews.author: Temaris Dixon
detailedReviews.text: I would leave zero stars if I had the option to. This restaurant is a disgrace to any restaurant owners across America. The level of racism is disgusting at this restaurant and if you are from anywhere outside of Ashland, Wisconsin, I advise you NOT to go here unless you want to be profiled against for being a minority. Highly unprofessional and I would not spend a PENNY at this establishment!

detailedReviews.author: Khyla
detailedReviews.text: I was racially profiled at this restaurant‚Ä¶..spoken to in broken English with my colleagues as a ‚Äújoke‚Äù and I was so embarrassed as I sat with my colleagues who were all white women ‚Ä¶. Being the only minority it was very clear what his motive was‚Ä¶ if I was able to leave  zero stars I would. IF YOU ARE A MINORITY FROM OUT OF TOWN please just go through a drive through. It was the first time in my 26 years of living that I was ever discriminated against ‚Ä¶.. call it what you want but ‚ÄúRACIST‚Äù is the FIRST thing that comes to MY mind ‚Ä¶. HIGHLY disappointed!!!!!!!!!

detailedReviews.text: This is the best fish and chips around just a little pricey

detailedReviews.author: Karen Keith
detailedReviews.text: Good

detailedReviews.author: Carol G
detailedReviews.text: We stopped here 2 days prior to this visit, but they were closed for an employee event.  So glad we came back!  The food was delicious and the service was great! Highly recommend the crab stuffed mushrooms and the cheese curd burger.  Also, the portions were generous.  We ordered an extra side of asparagus each, but could have easily split one, and the charge was very reasonable for this extra side.  We will definitely eat here again when we are in the area.  Thanks!

detailedReviews.author: Aaron McQuarter
detailedReviews.text:
So, service here is really hit or miss. I haven't been disappointed by the food, as long as you are willing to wait 45 minutes to an hour for it.

The service is another story. The staff here are less than friendly and can be outright rude. I don't care to wait an hour for food with poor service during the wait. I really want this place to be great but I can't tell you that it's even good...or that I will be back.

detailedReviews.author: Tracy Niemuth
detailedReviews.text: Great food and views.  Salad bar very big, soups and sandwiches tasty

detailedReviews.author: Joseph Kruckenberg
detailedReviews.text: Really good  were busy with the festival this week long wait  45 minutes but it was worth the wait. price of food very good will go back. hostess was new didn't know what was going on management  needs better training. I had the all you can eat fish fry fish was good tartar sauce a bit  to dilly but that's my taste.

detailedReviews.author: Linda Magnuson
detailedReviews.text: I was a little disappointed with my lunch. I wanted the mahi dish with salsa and they didn‚Äôt have the salsa. The salad bar didn‚Äôt have much for vegetables, mostly meat and salads that didn‚Äôt go on a lettuce salad. I thought the interior was not very trendy, but seemed clean.

detailedReviews.author: trisha b
detailedReviews.text: Had the steak it was good but a little grissely so maybe not the best cut. The loaded potatoes were amazing. Added the salad bar which was good, croutons weren't the freshest but other options were good. They need to add lighting over the salad bar, it's dark for a food area.

detailedReviews.author: Jodi Rush
detailedReviews.text:
Ordinarily, I like the place, but it really depends on what you order. I find their buffet to be bland and processed...avoid. The items I've ordered off the menu have been pretty good; Not great, but slightly better than average for this area.
My last visit, I had the soup & salad bar. Halfway through eating  my salad, I noticed a large clump of mud on my lettuce (ewww), so I showed the server and she went to the kitchen to tell them. Upon returning, she said they would check the salad bar...
I was seated directly facing the salad bar and nobody ever did come check it. Not only that, no manager came over to apologize and no comp was offered. This place is now off my go to list :(

detailedReviews.author: Carlos Cornay
detailedReviews.text:
We had lunch on Monday, Labor Day.. there was one server and one cook. We waited to be seated for approximately 10 minutes. There was 3 other tables having lunch. The food was fair. The server was busy and did what she could just to keep up.
The men‚Äôs restroom was disgusting . The urinals were awful. Strong smell and pubic hair on both. The sink area hadn‚Äôt been cleaned, floor was wet and dirty. It was very warm and smelly in the bathroom. You should keep the urinal full of ice. As it melts, it washes down the pee.

detailedReviews.author: Holly Bacha
detailedReviews.text: Food was delicious and reasonably priced. Awesome kid options. Great service.

detailedReviews.author: Tim Nemeth
detailedReviews.text: Took a chance on dinning at this place since we were visiting from out of town.  The food, service and atmosphere was exceptional!  Our server, Jacob, did a fantastic job!!!  He was very charismatic and knowledgeable of the menu and also offered us a fun treat after our meal.  We asked him for recommendations which were amazing like the shrimp lettuce wraps for an appetizer.  We got the ribeye to split with a side of wild mushrooms and loaded tator tots.  The steak alone was one of the best steaks we ate in our entire life!  Grilled perfectly to the medium-rare which we requested.   We loved the atmosphere.  It could be as formal or casual as you wished.  It was a beautiful setting on the golf course with beautiful views of the setting sun overlooking Chequamegon Bay.  I also liked the private booth we were seated in which made a wonderful evening for me and my wife.  A plus all around!  Great job to all that made our evening special!

detailedReviews.author: Austin Hebert
detailedReviews.text: Great place to grab some food any day of the week especially after some golfing!

detailedReviews.author: Aidan LaFrenier
detailedReviews.text: The servers were energetic and kind as well as helpful. The Restaurant looked nice and the food was delectable.

detailedReviews.author: Merel Kerr

detailedReviews.author: Judi Igo
detailedReviews.text: Very attentive wait staff

detailedReviews.author: Matt C
detailedReviews.text: In town for a few days and heard of this newer restaurant in the area. Server was very inattentive, no music playing, fries were rock hard. Would definitely not recommend.

detailedReviews.text: Great food and service. Nice atmosphere, and plenty of options!

detailedReviews.text: Great food and service.   Saturday evening for the Lions Club fund raiser and also Sunday after Church Great Breakfast Menu

detailedReviews.author: Lisa Ekman
detailedReviews.text: Excellent prime rib and salmon.  Wait staff is always excellent.

detailedReviews.author: Hessah Saleh
detailedReviews.text:
This is a little gem I found yesterday! The bartender/waitress was just a wonderful spirit that made it even more memorable. Food is great! Appetizers are fresh and awesome. My mom loved their lobster bisque. The fresh pretzel, cheese curds, onion rings‚Ä¶ mmm mmm mmm! I also enjoyed my virgin Bloody Mary and my son their apple cider juice.

I can‚Äôt wait to go back for another experience more focused on the rest of the menu.

detailedReviews.text: Natalie and staff served up delicious  food and attentive service and made our wedding anniversary extra special.  We will be back!

detailedReviews.text: Portions were great!! Service was great too! I would not recommend the crab cakes since it was mostly breading overly salty and I really didn't find and crab...maybe a little fishy flavor.

neutral.text: Being a tourist to Ashland, WI and counting this as one of my favorite cities to vacation, I can say there are much better places to eat in the area.  This is just okay.  Nothing to write home or even post about to be honest.  It is a golf course bar in a small blue collar town that serves food.  The food here is too much of a promise for the grill and not enough on follow-through.  Save your money and eat elsewhere.  This is a better place if you golf and just drink.

negative.author: Alexander Dempsey
negative.text: Quality has declined steeply over the past year to the point I don't know what to expect when I order. Too bad, because it was really great before. I get that food costs are up, but I'd rather pay more for the same quality than have it all downgraded to the point of undesirability.

negative.author: Oliver
negative.text: Our appetizer was fine, but their signature Alfredo was pretty bad. It was so bland, it tasted like watered-down garlic and nothing else.
